caption: What happened to this menu. This needs to change now

Not a satisfactory experience here. Came here to enjoy some shared plates and drinks with friends only to find that the food was quite overpriced, especially considering the amount of food you get. Ordered appetizers to share, including the brussel poutine ($7), the pig ears ($12), and the beet toast ($15). All three plates could be easily consumed in two bites and the brussel sprouts in the poutine were overcooked. The only redeeming factor here was the beer on tap, but that’s hardly something to praise a bar about especially when you come for food too. Our group left and had to find other food elsewhere since we were still starving. Wont be coming back.

No longer serve the burgers pictured in many reviews.  The menu is now a revolving menu that changes every few weeks.  The food was different than anything I have had before but it was delicious.  If you are looking for an eclectic menu, give it a try!

I don’t typically write negative reviews but this one has to be made.  This place went from being a 5 star restaurant to a 1 star in a matter of months! For the life of me I cannot understand the menu changes.  The burgers they used to sell were actually really good albeit pricey but still I don’t mind shelling out a little extra for good food.  This new concept is not only baffling it’s poorly executed. The only remnants of burgers is their “lonely burger” which is quite fitting considering all it comes with is the burger, which even if it was a massive burger would still be odd but it’s not it’s one step above a slider and served on a bun that looks like it came from Safeway.  Next was the fish sandwich which was so heavily seasoned with clove (really clove?!?!)  it literally tasted like a bowl of potpourri I got two bites in and couldn’t finish it. On top of that their sides are “ala carte” Aka we found another way to charge you extra for food that should already come with an entree.  That being said how can you have a fried fish sandwich and burger on your menu and not have fries as a side?! Instead the closest thing you can get is “smashed potatoes” which is funny considering they aren’t even smashed! It’s literally just fingerling potatoes stacked on top of each other and caked with some pepper flake, sauerkraut  and dried out chorizo.  The only saving grace this place now has is it’s atmosphere and drinks which is an absolute bummer because this was literally one of the best burger spots in town.  Now they’re serving this over thought “artisanal” menu that is not only out of touch it’s poorly executed.  Sadly the only real draw this place now has IMO is for a happy hour but considering they charge an arm and a leg for drinks (which I didn’t used to mind because the burgers were bomb) I can’t imagine they’re gunna last very long.  You guys had a good thing going, dunno why you had to change it, total bummer.

Opening: Decided to get dinner here on a Saturday night and for the most part it was bland this time around. It was all day happy hour on a Saturday so that was great though.  Dinner: My girlfriend whom I went out with had the Cheese steak sandwich with crunchy potato chips, which are always a good addition. I opted for the special of the day which was the Drive thru burger minus the fries since the special of the day was a burger and the 511 ale for $9.99. The 511 Session ale brewed by Square Barrels I believe and it was ok I would give it a 6/10. The burger was small but tasty. Our main meals were fine but our dessert the brownie Suffle was absolutely atrocious, the brownie tasted burned and dried out almost as if it spent longer than normal time in the microwave "baking". I would not recommend that dessert option to my worst enemy.  Beer: The menu selections for beer are overall pretty big which is always great especially considering I fancy myself a beer snob. I had the 511 session ale which was ok and the Pillbox porter from Lanikai brewing which was 8/10. The bloody marry that my girlfriend ordered seemed to taste great so there's another plus.  Issues: Here is where I talk about our rude and mouthy server Noel B. Upon arriving at Square Barrels he seemed fine and offered his favorites from the menu that he enjoyed. For some reason Noel B couldn't understand that I only ordered one 511 which is the one that comes with the burger. Somehow he thought I ordered  a second one and when I told him I was not drinking it he seemed to get upset about it. He even went so far as to say " I guess someone else is going to have to drink that beer" in the most condescending way. When he muttered that  I couldn't believe it, I'm a very reasonable customer but that very comment ruined my entire evening and dinner. For the rest of the evening I begrudgingly pushed thru and couldn't wait to leave this establishment. Noel B's comment made my blood boil, but I decided to keep it civil with him so as to not make things awkward and weird. After the beer ordeal Noel appeared disconnected and unwilling to fully interact with us out of pettiness I'm sure.  Conclusion: I will never go back to this establishment, the first 3 times my girlfriend and I had been here we had a great time, but dinner with our server last night was horrible and just ruined our Saturday evening.
